-- Inter, Napoli Gain Ground on Milan in Italian Soccer; Real Wins in Spain
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2011-02-06T23:29:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-06/napoli-gains-momentum-in-italian-soccer-real-madrid-wins-4-1-in-spain.html
Inter Milan and Napoli gained ground
in the Italian soccer standings with home victories as Serie A
leader AC Milan drew 1-1 at Genoa.  Samuel Eto’o scored twice and  Wesley Sneijder , Thiago Motta
and Esteban Cambiasso added the others in Inter’s 5-3 win over
Roma last night. Napoli earlier beat Cesena 2-0, with Edinson
Cavani and Jose Sosa getting the goals.  AC Milan, which led at Genoa through Alexandre Pato’s goal
before Antonio Floro Flores tied it, has 49 points, with Napoli
on 46 and defending champion Inter on 44. Lazio slipped to
fourth with 42 points after being held 1-1 at home by Chievo.  In Spain, Real Madrid stayed seven points behind Barcelona
with a 4-1 home win over Real Sociedad.  Kaka got Real Madrid’s opener and  Cristiano Ronaldo  added
two more goals before halftime. Alvaro Arbeloa scored an own
goal before Emmanuel Adebayor completed the scoring for Real in
the closing minutes.    Lionel Messi  scored a hat-trick two days ago as Barcelona
beat Atletico Madrid 3-0 to clinch a record 16th straight league
win, one ahead of the mark set by Real Madrid in 1960-61.    Borussia Dortmund , after a 0-0 draw in the Ruhr derby with
Schalke three days ago, leads by 12 points in  Germany . Second
placed Bayer Leverkusen lost 1-0 at Nuremberg two days ago.  Lille tops  France ’s Ligue 1 by five points after a 1-1 draw
at Auxerre yesterday.  In the Netherlands, FC Twente moved level on 47 points with
leader  PSV Eindhoven  after drawing 1-1 at FC Utrecht yesterday.
PSV lost 1-0 at home to Den Haag two days ago.  WEEKEND RESULTS
===============  Italy: Udinese 2-0 Sampdoria; Cagliari 1-3 Juventus; Bologna 1-0
Catania; Brescia 2-0 Bari; Genoa 1-1 AC Milan; Lazio 1-1 Chievo;
Lecce 2-4 Palermo; Napoli 2-0 Cesena; Parma 1-1 Fiorentina;
Inter Milan 5-3 Roma.    Spain : Osasuna 1-1 Mallorca; Almeria 3-2 Espanyol; Athletic
Bilbao 3-0 Sporting Gijon; Getafe 4-1 Deportivo La Coruna; Real
Zaragoza 1-1 Racing Santander; Villarreal 0-1 Levante; Barcelona
3-0 Atletico Madrid; Sevilla 0-0 Malaga; Real Madrid 4-1 Real
Sociedad; Valencia 2-0 Hercules.  Germany: Borussia Dortmund 0-0 Schalke; Mainz 1-1 Werder Bremen;
Hoffenheim 3-2 Kaiserslautern; Cologne 3-2 Bayern Munich;
Hanover 1-0 Wolfsburg; Nuremberg 1-0 Bayer Leverkusen; Borussia
Moenchengladbach 2-3 Stuttgart; Hamburg v St. Pauli (postponed,
field waterlogged); Freiburg 0-0 Eintracht Frankfurt.  France: Marseille 1-0 Arles-Avignon; Montpellier 1-2 Saint-
